      <hedline>
        <hl1>Aid to the Palestinians</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jerome M Balsam letter on negative Palestinian reaction to US aid offer linked to signing of peace agreement says Palestinians should understand that aid is not an entitlement (Sept 20 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The Palestinian official Abu Mazen has expressed some shock that the United States would offer increased aid if the Palestinians were to sign a peace agreement and reduced aid should they fail to do so (news article, Sept. 20).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The Palestinian official Abu Mazen has expressed some shock that the United States would offer increased aid if the Palestinians were to sign a peace agreement and reduced aid should they fail to do so (news article, Sept. 20).</p>
        <p>There are two valuable lessons here for the nascent Palestinian state: foreign aid is not an entitlement, and incentives matter. One can only hope that the Palestinians absorb these lessons quickly enough to accept the deal offered by Israel at Camp David.</p>
        <p>JEROME M. BALSAM  New York, Sept. 20, 2000</p>
      </block>
